1.	sudo su  - root user 
2.	cd  - enter into the directory
3.	cd.. -  exit directory
4.	whoami -  to view current user
5.	pwd -  to see present working directory
6.	ls  -  lists the number of files and directory
7.	ls –lart -  see all the hidden files
8.	mkdir  -  create directory 
9.	rmdir - remove directory
10.	echo  -  view or call the file or directory
11.	cat -  create the file
12.	touch 
i.	create file
13.	cp- copy file
14.	mv- move or rename file
15.	rm- remove file
16.	chmod- change file or directory permission
17.	chown- change owner
18.	vi- enter the editor
19.	yum- package installer
20.	grep- search  the file
21.	find -  search specifically in file
22.	head- view first 10 lines
23.	tail- view last 10 lines
24.	history- displays all the used command/ history of command used
25.	useradd- add user
26.	userdel-delete user
27.	groupadd- add group
28.	groupdel- delete group
29.	clear- clears the screen
30.	rm –rf- deletes everything 
31.	sort – to sort the files in alphabetical order
32.	cal- to view the calendar
33.	date  - view the date
34.	time – view time
35.	git add-add files to github
36.	git status- view the status of git
37.	git commit-commit the git to branch
38.	git checkout -create branch
39.	git push -push the git to github

